Each run counts towards your total. Simple classing and typically a lot of runs.\n\nDon\u2019t get me wrong, I like autocross (Ax) and track days and w2w racing (and have done all of them for a long time!), but Rx is a lot of fun as well. Horsepower and tires are less important and driving skill even more at a premium.\n\nAx Pro = Fun, get to push the car hard in a safe place, learn good skills that can transfer to the street\nAx Con = Tires critical for good results, accelerated wear on tires\n\nRx Pro = Fun, learn good skills, similar to racing in the rain, very easy on tires and car\nRxCon = Farther away (although they hold them in the field at TWS), might need to wash car when done (but you like spending time with your car, so that's not really a con...)\n\nTrackDay/W2W Pro = Higher speeds = more fun, sessions can last 20+ minutes\nTrackDay/W2W Con = Much more expensive, harder on equipment, some no-talent @$$ clown can wreck into you and seriously mess up your car or you can simply mess it up yourself if you\u2019re in over your head. \n\nI just did my first ever Rx recently at the RxNats in Tulsa = http://www.witchdoctormotorsports.com/ch213.htm and I\u2019m telling you that I\u2019ll for sure attend more of these as my schedule permits. {"from": {"id": "1521481724", "name": "Cody Walker"}, "privacy": {"value": ""}, "actions": [{"link": "https://www.facebook.com/2200384508/posts/10151405858359509", "name": "Like"}], "updated_time": "2013-02-06T05:16:30+0000", "to": {"data": [{"name": "Texas A&M Sports Car Club (TAMSCC)", "id": "2200384508"}]}, "likes": {"paging": {"cursors": {"after": "NzI5MDg2MDcy", "before": "NzI5MDg2MDcy"}}, "data": [{"id": "729086072", "name": "Christopher Massey"}]}, "created_time": "2013-02-05T17:08:29+0000", "message": "Rallye 2 Spring 2013\n \nWhen? Friday, Feb. 8, 2013\n Where: 6:45@ Area 51, 7:00 Driver's Meeting, 7:15 First Car Out\n \n*Times are approximate, which is ironic when you consider the event...*\n \nSay hello to natural progression, have fun. \n\nCome join us for a fun night of driving aimlessly through town and the countryside! Rallyes are a great event for discovering the town, making stories, getting lost, and just plain having a good time. Plus there's a gathering at the end... so... yeah.\n\nWhat is this rallye business?\n\n Our rallyes are a Time Speed Distance rallye. You are given a set of coded directions (SSS = Straight at Stop Sign, R1 = First right, etc). Your objective is to make it through the directions. However, you also are trying to get through the directions to each of 3 checkpoints in the ideal amount of time (based on how far it is between checkpoints and what your average speed (CAST) is on those roads). THIS IS NOT A RACE. Getting there first doesn't make you the winner. Speeds are even set 5 MPH below the legal speed limit. You get points for every second early or late you are. Lowest score wins. This all sounds really complicated, but it's a blast. If you're new, don't worry. Just making it to the finish is quite an accomplishment and gives you a good shot at winning a trophy! There is an expert and novice class, so you won't be competing against people that have done this for 4 years. \n\nDown to business: What to bring?\n Driver: Full gas tank (be ready to drive at least 80 miles).\n Navigator: Clipboard, pen/pencil, flashlight.\n Also, you can pile in as many people as you want, or legally can, into your car!\n \nONLY EXPERT CLASS IS ALLOWED TO HAVE A GPS!\n \nPrices are (per car) Members $5, Non-Members $10.", "type": "status", "id": "2200384508_10151405858359509", "comments": {"paging": {"cursors": {"after": "MTAxNTE0MDY5MTk3OTQ1MDk=", "before": "MTAxNTE0MDU4NjQyNDQ1MDk="}}, "data": [{"from": {"id": "1358905181", "name": "Dennis Wittekind"}, "like_count": 0, "can_remove": false, "created_time": "2013-02-05T17:09:38+0000", "message": "w00t!", "id": "10151405864244509", "user_likes": false}, {"from": {"id": "34408857", "name": "Ryan Rhino Russell"}, "like_count": 0, "can_remove": false, "created_time": "2013-02-05T17:10:40+0000", "message": "Boooooooooo", "id": "10151405865519509", "user_likes": false}, {"from": {"id": "729086072", "name": "Christopher Massey"}, "like_count": 0, "can_remove": false, "created_time": "2013-02-06T04:44:29+0000", "message": "how long do these usually last? and this may be a stupid question, but I assume times are PM and not AM? >.>", "id": "10151406888489509", "user_likes": false}, {"from": {"id": "8336172", "name": "Chad Kuboviak"}, "like_count": 1, "can_remove": false, "created_time": "2013-02-06T05:16:30+0000", "message": "There are no stupid questions!
